--- INSTALL ---
install vala and build app usual way
make
make install
#TODO(vasaka) geather dependencies here
--- RUN ---
v4lsink

if you have 640x480 webcam at /dev/video0 you can check result with command
if you want another resolution - change it in gst-v4lsink-loopback.vala
$mplayer tv:// -tv device=/dev/video1
or $luvcview -d /dev/video1 -f yuv
or just select /dev/video1 in skype and transmit fun video

you also can pass custom pipeline with fancy video filters as command line parameter last element in pipelene shoul be v4lSinkLoopback

default pipeline is 'v4l2src device=/dev/video0 ! ffmpegcolorspace ! v4lSinkLoopback'
if you want to use some effect filters - run this:
v4lsink 'v4l2src device=/dev/video0 ! ffmpegcolorspace ! effect ! ffmpegcolorspace ! V4l2SinkLoopback'

effect is any registered gstreamer vido effect plugin, warptv for example 